{"name": "byrdocs-cli", "metadata": {"name": "byrdocs-cli", "version": "0.3.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/byrdocs/byrdocs-cli", "license": "MIT License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests", "boto3", "botocore", "argcomplete", "tqdm", "InquirerPy", "pyyaml", "isbnlib"], "summary": "A simple command line tool for BYR Docs", "upload_time": 1732182678}, "documentation": ["# BYR Docs CLI\n\n## Install \n\n### Using pip:\n```bash\npip3 install byrdocs-cli\n```\n\n### Using pipx (alternated, when you have problem with pip):\n\nChoose one of the following commands according to your package manager:\n```bash\nsudo apt install pipx\nsudo dnf install pipx\nsudo pacman -S pipx\n```\n\nThen:\n```\npipx install byrdocs-cli    \n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```\nusage: byrdocs [-h] [--token TOKEN] [command] [file]\n\nCommands:\n  upload <file>    Upload a file. If no command is specified, it defaults to upload.\n  login            Authenticate with BYR Docs and obtain a token.\n  logout           Remove the locally stored authentication token.\n\npositional arguments:\n  command        Command to execute\n  file           Path to the file to upload\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help     show this help message and exit\n  --token TOKEN  Token for login command\n\nExamples:\n $ byrdocs login\n $ byrdocs /home/exam_paper.pdf\n $ byrdocs logout\n```\n\n## Development\n\nBuild:\n\n```bash\npython3 -m build\n```\n\n\nPush to PyPI:\n```bash\npython3 -m twine upload --repository pypi dist/* --verbose\n```\n\nTest:\n```bash\npython test.py [arguments]\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "byrdocs.yaml_init", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "byrdocs.yaml_init.not_empty", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "content", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "byrdocs.yaml_init.is_vaild_year", "asyn